  <title>Importing and Exporting</title>

  <section id="import">
    <title>Importing Audio</title>
    <p>You can import existing audio files as new tracks:</p>
    <steps>
      <item><p>Select <guiseq><gui>Menu</gui><gui>Import Audio…</gui></guiseq> or press 
      <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>I</key></keyseq>.</p></item>
      <item><p>Select a WAV file from your computer.</p></item>
      <item><p>A new track is created with the imported audio.</p></item>
    </steps>
    <note>
      <p>Currently, only WAV files can be imported.</p>
    </note>
  </section>

  <section id="export-tracks">
    <title>Export Individual Tracks</title>
    <p>Export each track as a separate file:</p>
    <steps>
      <item><p>Select <guiseq><gui>Menu</gui><gui>Export Tracks…</gui></guiseq> or press 
      <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>Shift</key><key>T</key></keyseq>.</p></item>
      <item><p>Choose a destination folder.</p></item>
      <item><p>Each track is saved as a WAV file named after the track.</p></item>
    </steps>
  </section>

  <section id="export-mixed">
    <title>Export Mixed</title>
    <p>Combine all tracks into a single audio file:</p>
    <steps>
      <item><p>Select <guiseq><gui>Menu</gui><gui>Export Mixed…</gui></guiseq> or press 
      <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>Shift</key><key>X</key></keyseq>.</p></item>
      <item><p>Choose a filename and location.</p></item>
      <item><p>All tracks are mixed together and saved as one WAV file.</p></item>
    </steps>
    <note style="tip">
      <p>The mixed export combines all tracks. Muted tracks are still included 
      in the mix. To exclude a track from the mix, delete it first or export 
      tracks individually.</p>
    </note>
  </section>

  <section id="export-all">
    <title>Export All</title>
    <p>Export both individual tracks and a mixed version:</p>
    <steps>
      <item><p>Select <guiseq><gui>Menu</gui><gui>Export All…</gui></guiseq> or press 
      <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>Shift</key><key>A</key></keyseq>.</p></item>
      <item><p>Choose a destination folder.</p></item>
      <item><p>The folder will contain individual WAV files for each track, 
      plus a <file>mixed.wav</file> file with all tracks combined.</p></item>
    </steps>
  </section>

